notes: On 1 November 2023, about 500 farmers with more than 130 tractors and trucks participated in a protest in front of the state parliament in Dresden (Sachsen) on the call of the initiative 'Land schafft Verbindung' (Land creates connection) against the delayed disbursement of EU funds in the state of Saxony from December to February. The protest was organized in parallel to a committee meeting concerned with the issue in the building. Earlier in the morning, farmers with a little more than 80 tractors gathered on a parking lot in Lonnewith at the B6 to participate in a protest drive to Dresden for the demonstration.
notes_wrapped:

connection) against the delayed disbursement of EU

a committee meeting concerned with the issue in
the building. Earlier in the morning, farmers with
a little more than 80 tractors gathered on a
parking lot in Lonnewith at the B6 to participate
in a protest drive to Dresden for the
demonstration.

One tractor driver tried to break through a barrier, slightly injuring a police officer, and was taken to the police station. The event was peaceful and a convoy from Netphen joined the protest.

notes: On 10 January 2024, farmers with several tractors demonstrated by driving up to the Congress Hall in Boblingen (Baden-Wurttemberg) against the planned abolition of diesel subsidies and the tax exemption for agricultural and forestry machinery. One demonstrator drove her tractor in the direction of a police officer and pushed him at walking speed for a few meters. The 20-year-old tractor driver only stopped after a patrol car was positioned in front of her. She resisted her subsequent arrest and faced criminal charges for dangerous interference with road traffic, coercion, and resisting law enforcement officers at the time of reporting.

notes: On 26 January 2024, a large group of farmers, agricultural workers, entrepreneurs, residents, and students took to the streets in Pescara (Abruzzo) to protest against the EU's agricultural policies. notes: On 24 January 2024, more than 100 French farmers from CR, accompanied by some Dutch farmers from the FarmerCitizenMovement (BoerBurgerBeweging) and Italian farmers from the CGIL, gathered in front of the European Parliament in Brussels - Ixelles (Brussels) to protest against the excesses of the European agricultural policy. More specifically, they denounce increases in taxes, fuel prices and animal food costs as well as an overzealous application of European directives. The Mathias Corvinus Collegium and Hungarian farmers organized an event during the demonstration, where a representative of the Farmers Alliance Ireland spoke about building a European coalition of farmers.
notes_wrapped:

(Brussels) to protest against the excesses of the
European agricultural policy. More specifically,
they denounce increases in taxes, fuel prices and
animal food costs as well as an overzealous
application of European directives. The Mathias
Corvinus Collegium and Hungarian farmers organized
an event during the demonstration, where a
representative of the Farmers Alliance Ireland
spoke about building a European coalition of
farmers.

notes: On 23 January 2024, about 4,000 people, including farmers, members of the association 'Agriculture connects Bayern' (Landwirtschaft verbindet Bayern), mayor Tobias Eschenbach, District Administrator Helmut Petz and Bundestag Member Andreas Mehltretter (SPD), participated in a protest in Freising (Bayern) called for by GJ and Jusos, against far-right extremism, inhumanity and anti-democractic attitudes. The protest was part of a nationwide protest movement after recent reports of a secret meeting between AfD members and right-wing extremists in Potsdam past November.

notes: On 23 January 2024, in the morning, farmers set up a road blockade on the RN20 road in Pamiers (Nouvelle-Aquitaine) to demonstrate. The event was part of a nationwide farmers' demonstration movement called by FNSEA and JA against rising production costs, stricter environmental norms restricting the use of pesticides, foreign imports, and bureaucratic constraints. A car driven by Armenian nationals traveling toward Andorra crashed into a wall of straw bales erected behind a tent where demonstrators had gathered, killing a 36-year-old female farmer instantly, and grievously injuring her 39-year-old husband and her 12-year-old daughter, who died from her injuries at the hospital the following day. The car driver (a man who was subject to an obligation to leave French territory (OQTF) at the time) was arrested and awaiting his trial (as of 23 July 2024), and that his family was expelled from France on 21 June 2024.
notes_wrapped:

(Nouvelle-Aquitaine) to demonstrate. The event was
part of a nationwide farmers' demonstration
movement called by FNSEA and JA against rising
production costs, stricter environmental norms
restricting the use of pesticides, foreign
imports, and bureaucratic constraints. A car
driven by Armenian nationals traveling toward
Andorra crashed into a wall of straw bales erected
behind a tent where demonstrators had gathered,
killing a 36-year-old female farmer instantly, and
grievously injuring her 39-year-old husband and
her 12-year-old daughter, who died from her
injuries at the hospital the following day. The
car driver (a man who was subject to an obligation
to leave French territory (OQTF) at the time) was
arrested and awaiting his trial (as of 23 July
2024), and that his family was expelled from
France on 21 June 2024.

notes: On 23 January 2024, about 100 farmers demonstrated in Verona (Veneto) to protest against the EU's agricultural policies. Demonstrators also protested against high production costs, subsidy cuts to their sector, laboratory-made meat, flour produced using insects, and regulations on imported agricultural products, among other things. Representatives of the newly formed CRA - Committee of Betrayed Farmers (Comitato Agricoltori Traditi) attended the gathering.

There were verbal confrontations between police and the farmers' representatives. Negotiations to allow farmers to protest on the road on foot also failed.

notes: On 24 January 2024, around 3000 farmers from all over Lithuania protested outside of the Government Office in Vilnius, Lithuania, calling against the government's agricultural policy which creates unfavourable conditions for farming. This 2-day protest is the continuation of the nationwide farmer protests that took place in early January. Around one thousand tractors and forestry trucks that the farmers drove to Vilnius as part of the protest action lined Gediminas Avenue in central Vilnius.

notes: On 24 January 2024, more than 200 farmers rode with their tractors through the streets of Bastia Umbra (Umbria) to protest against the EU's agricultural policies. Demonstrators also protested against high production costs, subsidy cuts to their sector, laboratory-made meat, flour produced using insects, and regulations on imported agricultural products, among other things. Representatives of the newly formed CRA - Committee of Betrayed Farmers (Comitato Agricoltori Traditi) and regional councilor Stefano Pastorelli (Lega) attended the demonstration.

notes: On 31 January 2024, farmers with 8 tractors and some cars participated in a motorcade in Alcanices (Zamora, Castilla y Leon), subsequently riding along the N122 road in the direction of the border with Portugal. The event was part of a nationwide farmers' demonstration movement called by ASAJA, COAG, and UPA against the ratification of the EU's free-trade agreements until partner third countries comply with the EU's agricultural standards, and in favor of fair production prices for Spanish farmers, relief measures to offset the consequences of droughts and of the import of agricultural products from Ukraine, as well as better working and social conditions in their sector.

notes: On 1 February 2024, farmers with hundreds of tractors participated in a motorcade around Leon (Castilla y Leon), attempting to enter the city. The event was part of a nationwide farmers' demonstration movement called by ASAJA, COAG, and UPA against the ratification of the EU's free-trade agreements until partner third countries comply with the EU's agricultural standards, and in favor of fair production prices for Spanish farmers, relief measures to offset the consequences of droughts and of the import of agricultural products from Ukraine, as well as better working and social conditions in their sector.

notes: On 30 January 2024, 400 tractors as convoys from across the Center of Italy gathered at the Valdichiana toll booth in Bettolle (Siena). Protesters waved tricolor flags and displayed banners with the words 'You will be uncultivated, not my land', 'Let's cultivate a future, not hope', 'Let's fight for everyone, if we fail there will be no future'. The event was part of a nationwide farmers' demonstration movement called by Agrarian Redemption against the government's plan to cut agricultural sector subsidies, the economic difficulties of the sector, and the EU policies regarding agriculture and livestock.

notes: On 29 January 2024, farmers, including farmers whose fields were still covered in floodwater, and livestock breeders protesting over high production costs, among other issues they said are pertinent to their survival, rallied at Platykambos with about 600 tractors. They were also joined by another 160 tractors from an earlier protest in central Larissa. Following brief negotiations with the police, who refused to allow them to block the road with their tractors, they blocked the road on foot in a surprise move and they protested over 'police repression'. They said they didn't want to block traffic, they just wanted to prove they could and demanded to negotiate with the PM himself and not the agriculture minister.

notes: On 2 February 2024, at 5:30 am, around 60 farmers, with around 40 agricultural vehicles, gathered on the A2 freeway at the entrance to Zweidorfer Holz, blocked three lanes, and drove their vehicles in a convoy to Peine (Niedersachsen). After leaving the motorway, farmers gathered at the Peine truck stop and then drove together through the northern district to their homes (Uelzen, Gifhorn, and Celle). The event was part of a nationwide farmers' demonstration movement against several agricultural policies of the federal government, including planned agricultural subsidy cuts.

notes: On 2 February 2024, farmers, mostly from Western Macedonia, protesting over high production costs, among other issues they said are pertinent to their survival, lined up with about 360 tractors at the gates of the Thessaloniki International Fair exhibition center hosting the 30th International Agriculture Fair 'Agrotica'. The protesters said they were not satisfied with the measures announced by the prime minister, which included tax rebates, a five- month discount on electricity rates, debt relief and a promise to speed up the delivery of flood recovery funds in central Greece, describing them as 'a drop in the ocean', and they closed 1 of the gates to the exhibition center.

notes: On 3 February 2024, a good 30,000 people (according to police) or a good 35,000 people (according to the organizers), State Secretary Siegfried Lorek (CDU), CDU State Director Tobias Vogt and Financial Mayor Stefan Breiter (CDU), district chairman of the SPD, members of the State Parliament for the Greens, trade unions, churches, companies and schools, as well as some farmers, members of the Italian community, Antifa, 'Nature Friends Germany' (Naturfreunde Deutschlands), representatives of the German Council for Refugees and the Baden Agricultural Association, participated in a protest in Freiburg im Breisgau (Baden-Wurttemberg) called for by an alliance of private people and supported by more than 500 organizations, including 'Grannies and Grandpas Against the Right' (Omas und Opas Gegen Rechts', FFF, 'Baden Agricultural Main Association' (Badischer Landwirtschaflicher Hauptverband) and the sport club Freiburg to set a sign against far-right extremism. The protest was organized following reports about a secret meeting between AfD members and far-right activists in Potsdam in November 2023, during which remigration plans were discussed.

notes: On 3 February 2024, hundreds of farmers from Thessaly arrived on buses and joined the farmers of Central Macedonia, who were protesting with 300 tractors outside the south gate of the Thessaloniki International Fair (TIF) during the Agrotica exhibition over rising production costs, among other issues they said are pertinent to their survival. They threw chestnuts and apples on the street and then marched to the TIF grounds, holding banners and shouting slogans. They were supported by their federations and students, who were opposing the government's draft bill for the establishment of private universities. They held speeches. The previous day the Greek government rushed out a new support package including tax rebates, a five- month discount on electricity rates, debt relief and a promise to speed up the delivery of flood recovery funds in central Greece, but protesting farmers said it was 'a drop in the ocean' and that they would continue their demonstrations. Following the protest, the Thessalian farmers left, but the farmers from northern Greece stayed on. The government ruled out additional support.

notes: On 1 February 2024, hundreds of farmers, stockbreeders and beekeepers from various parts of Central Macedonia rallied in Thessaloniki, where they lined up more than 400 tractors at the south gate of the Thessaloniki International Fair exhibition center hosting the 30th International Agriculture Fair 'Agrotica', demanding solutions to their problems and greater support for the farming sector. They were also joined by fishers who docked their boats on the Thessaloniki waterfront. The protesters honked their horns, carried banners and Greek flags, and a black coffin symbolizing the death of the farming sector, but they did not block the entrance to Agrotica. Their representatives held speeches before submitting a memorandum at the Ministry of Macedonia and Thrace.
notes_wrapped:
On 1 February 2024, hundreds of farmers,
stockbreeders and beekeepers from various parts of
Central Macedonia rallied in Thessaloniki, where

gate of the Thessaloniki International Fair
exhibition center hosting the 30th International
Agriculture Fair 'Agrotica', demanding solutions
to their problems and greater support for the
farming sector. They were also joined by fishers
who docked their boats on the Thessaloniki
waterfront. The protesters honked their horns,
carried banners and Greek flags, and a black
coffin symbolizing the death of the farming
sector, but they did not block the entrance to

before submitting a memorandum at the Ministry of
Macedonia and Thrace.

notes: On 1 February 2024, around 3,000 people, including local politicians, elected officials, representatives of churches, students, union members, and one farmer with a tractor, demonstrated from the main square to the Zur Tiefenbach barrel factor in Hachenburg (Rheinland-Pfalz), against right-wing extremism. They called for the political party AfD to be banned and the closure of the barrel factory, where Eastern European war prisoners were forced to work as forced laborers during the Second World War, which is now classified by the Office for the Protection of the Constitution as a meeting place for far-right groups such as The Third Path political party. The protest was organized following reports about a secret meeting between AfD members and far-right activists in Potsdam in November 2023, during which remigration plans were discussed.

On 1 February 2024, around 3,000 people, including

members, and one farmer with a tractor,

Pfalz), against right-wing extremism. They called
for the political party AfD to be banned and the

notes: On 8 February 2024, about 200 farmers with tractors participated in a motorcade in Burgos (Castilla y Leon), blocking the AP-1 near Rubena. The Civil Guard intervened to break up the protesters and arrested two people. The event was part of a nationwide farmers' demonstration movement called by UdU against the ratification of the EU's free-trade agreements until partner third countries comply with the EU's agricultural standards, and in favor of fair production prices for Spanish farmers, relief measures to offset the consequences of droughts and of the import of agricultural products from Ukraine, as well as better working and social conditions in their sector.

notes: On 8 February 2024, around 50 farmers staged a protest with their cars and tractors in front of the entrance 'Nordsee-Zeitung' printing press in Bremerhaven (Bremen), dumping manure, advocating against the policies of the German federal government, demanding agricultural policy changes, including opposing planned taxes on Agrardiesel and advocating for fairer producer prices and structural reforms in the food industry. notes: Around 10 February 2024, 300 farmers with tractors held a protest in Valdivia (Extremadura), blocking the N430 road. Members of the Extremadura branch ASAJA, The Extremadura Union (La Union Extremadura) and ASEPREX attended the protest. The event was part of a nationwide farmers' demonstration movement called by ASAJA, COAG, and UPA against the ratification of the EU's free-trade agreements until partner third countries comply with the EU's agricultural standards, and in favor of fair production prices for Spanish farmers, relief measures to offset the consequences of droughts and of the import of agricultural products from Ukraine, as well as better working and social conditions in their sector. Clashes ensued between the demonstrators and the police, with demonstrators throwing stones at the police. The police used tear gas and rubber bullets to dissuade the demonstrators

notes: On 6 February 2024, farmers with tractors participated in a motorcade in Fondarella (Cataluna), blocking the A2 highway. The event was part of a nationwide farmers' demonstration movement, called by UdU on that day, against the ratification of the EU's free-trade agreements until partner third countries comply with the EU's agricultural standards, and in favor of fair production prices for Spanish farmers, relief measures to offset the consequences of droughts and the import of agricultural products from Ukraine, as well as better working and social conditions in their sector.

notes: On 5 February 2024, around 400 people, including pensioners, farmers and other entrepreneurs, with about 175 tractors and 30 cars participated in a protest in Kempten (Allgau) (Bayern) and blocked the access roads to a media center in Heisinger Strasse to express their dissatisfaction with media coverage. The participants also protested against distortion of competition due to high tolls, against bureaucracy and CO2 taxes. The event was part of a nationwide farmers' demonstration movement against several agricultural policies of the federal government, including planned agricultural subsidy cuts.

notes: On 5 February 2024, about 40 farmers from the Nea Moudania blockade, protesting over rising production costs, among other issues they said are pertinent to their survival, set off for Thessaloniki with their tractors. They aimed to submit a resolution at the Ministry of Macedonia and Thrace, but MAT riot police set up a roadblock preventing the farmers from entering the city. Farmers were allowed to protest in the city in their vehicles, while they blocked one lane of the national road with their tractors.

notes: On 5 February 2024, 80 people, including farmers and members of the middle-class, with around 50 vehicles, including 30 tractors, participated in a protest in Hannover (Niedersachsen) and blocked the access road to the state broadcasting center of the North German Broadcasting Corporation (NDR) to criticize that media reports about the farmers' protests were minimal. The protesters led vehicles pass through. The event was part of a nationwide farmers' demonstration movement against several agricultural policies of the federal government, including planned agricultural subsidy cuts.

notes: On 7 February 2024, farmers with tractors participated in a motorcade from the N-122 in Borja, via the A-2 in Epila, the N-2 between Movera and Puebla de Alfindeny to Bujaraloz (Aragon). The event was part of a nationwide farmers' demonstration movement called by UdU against the ratification of the EU's free-trade agreements until partner third countries comply with the EU's agricultural standards, and in favor of fair production prices for Spanish farmers, relief measures to offset the consequences of droughts and of the import of agricultural products from Ukraine, as well as better working and social conditions in their sector.

notes: On 14 February 2024, about 400 farmers with tractors participated in a motorcade in Madridejos (Castilla-La Mancha), blocking the A-4 road. The event was part of a nationwide farmers' demonstration movement called by ASAJA, COAG, UPA and Agri-Food Cooperatives (Cooperativas Agro-alimentarias) against the ratification of the EU's free-trade agreements until partner third countries comply with the EU's agricultural standards, and in favor of fair production prices for Spanish farmers, relief measures to offset the consequences of droughts and of the import of agricultural products from Ukraine, as well as better working and social conditions in their sector.

farmers' demonstration movement called by ASAJA,

agricultural products from Ukraine, as well as
better working and social conditions in their
sector.

notes: On 14 February 2024, about 250 farmers participated in a protest in Aranda del Duero (Castilla y Leon), blocking the A-1 road. Civil guard officers tried to physically remove the protesters. One of them was arrested after confronting them. Nearly 100 farmers then protested near the police station of Aranda del Duero to call for the liberation of the arrested farmer. The event was part of a nationwide farmers' demonstration movement against the ratification of the EU's free-trade agreements until partner third countries comply with the EU's agricultural standards, and in favor of fair production prices for Spanish farmers, relief measures to offset the consequences of droughts and of the import of agricultural products from Ukraine, as well as better working and social conditions in their sector.

notes: On 17 February 2024, around 1,500 people, including numerous mayors (CDU), State Parliament Members (SPD & CDU), the former Minister of the Interior, representatives of the catholic and protestant church, DGB representatives, members of the Greens and FW, a school principal, and members of the German Farmers' Association, participated in a protest in Nastatten (Rheinland-Pfalz). The protest was organized under the motto 'Rhein-Lahn-District stands up against the Right' against racism, right-wing extremism and xenophobia. The protest was organized following reports about a secret meeting between AfD members and far-right activists in Potsdam in November 2023, during which remigration plans were discussed.

notes: On 13 February 2024, around 100 tractors rode from Salento (Puglia) to the Park Perotti in Bari (Puglia). Five tractors reached the headquarters of the Regional Council and asked to meet the president of the regional Assembly, Loredana Capone. The event is part of a nationwide farmers' demonstration movement called by RA against the government's plan to cut agricultural sector subsidies, the economic difficulties of the sector, and the EU policies regarding agriculture and livestock.

notes: On 22 February 2024, more than 500 beekeepers from across the country rallied at Syntagma square, Athens - Central Athens, with their vehicles to protest over high production costs and the unfair competition from imported honey labelled as Greek. Santaliestra y San Quilez (Aragon), blocking the
A-139. The event was part of a nationwide farmers'
demonstration movement against the ratification of
the EU's free-trade agreements until partner third
countries comply with the EU's agricultural
standards, and in favor of fair production prices
for Spanish farmers, relief measures to offset the
consequences of droughts and of the import of
agricultural products from Ukraine, as well as
better working and social conditions in their
sector.

farmers, including CR affiliates, gathered in
Paris (Ile-de-France), some reaching as tractor
convoys from across the region, to demonstrate.
The tractors blocked several regions of the city.
The event was part of a nationwide farmers'
demonstration movement, organized on the eve of
France's Agricultural Show, against rising
production costs, stricter environmental norms
restricting the use of pesticides, foreign
imports, and bureaucratic constraints.

notes: On 19 February 2024, at least 8,000 farmers (according to police estimates), livestock breeders and beekeepers from Evros to Crete participated in a mass nationwide rally with about 248 tractors outside parliament, Athens - Central Athens, protesting over rising costs, competition from abroad, the recent flooding in Thessaly and climate change-driven weather in general. They also criticized the substantial markup in shelf prices compared to what wholesalers paid them for their produce. Many protested over fuel costs, as farmers were paying more than three times as much for petrol as shipping companies due to tax disparities. They demanded a renegotiation of the EU's new Common Agricultural Policy (CAP) and called for more support by the government. Initially, the government barred farmers from descending to the capital with their tractors, but implemented emergency traffic measures instead. Police patrol cars escorted convoys of tractors as they moved on the national highways since the day before and blocked much of central Athens to motorists and public transport. More farmers arrived in their own vehicles, at least 100 coaches, and ferries from the islands. Some carried mock coffins and funeral wreaths. In a show of solidarity, citizens waved in the streets and hundreds of students joined the farmers and also protested government plans to introduce private universities in the country. Leading members and MPs of SYRIZA and 15 PASOK MPs were present. Trade unions also participated following a call by federation ADEDY. More than 10,000 attended according to demonstrators' estimates. Many farmers spent the night at Syntagma square and left the following day to return with their tractors to their highway blockades across the country.

Police patrol cars escorted convoys of tractors as

notes: On 21 February 2024, farmers from across the region with around 2,000 agricultural vehicles, called by ASAJA, COAG and UPA, participated in a motorcade through the Murcia region, before gathering in Murcia (Murcia), where around 200 tractors and 81 trucks took part in a motorcade through the city's streets. They called for the application of the Food Chain Law, the updating of the Law for the Protection and Recovery of the Mar Menor, as well as the implementation of measures against drought such as, for example, guaranteeing the continuity of the Tajo-Segura water transfer. The event was part of a nationwide farmers' demonstration movement.

notes: On 29 February 2024, half a thousand farmers, called by Platform for the Defense of the Countryside (Plataforma para la Defensa del Campo), held a protest in Merida (Extremadura) demanding long-term solutions for their sector. The event was part of a nationwide farmers' demonstration movement against the ratification of the EU's free-trade agreements until partner third countries comply with the EU's agricultural standards, and in favor of fair production prices for Spanish farmers, relief measures to offset the consequences of droughts and of the import of agricultural products from Ukraine, as well as better working and social conditions in their sector.
notes_wrapped:
On 29 February 2024, half a thousand farmers,
called by Platform for the Defense of the
Countryside (Plataforma para la Defensa del
Campo), held a protest in Merida (Extremadura)
demanding long-term solutions for their sector.
The event was part of a nationwide farmers'
demonstration movement against the ratification of
the EU's free-trade agreements until partner third
countries comply with the EU's agricultural
standards, and in favor of fair production prices
for Spanish farmers, relief measures to offset the
consequences of droughts and of the import of
agricultural products from Ukraine, as well as
better working and social conditions in their
sector.

Farmers dumped lemons on the street and threw lemons at the facade of the building which forced the police to shield the entrance of the building. The event was part of a nationwide farmers' demonstration movement against the ratification of the EU's free-trade agreements until partner third countries comply with the EU's agricultural standards, and in favor of fair production prices for Spanish farmers, relief measures to offset the consequences of droughts and of the import of agricultural products from Ukraine, as well as better working and social conditions in their sector.

notes: On 22 March 2024, around 500 farmers, called by ASAJA, COAG and UPA, held a protest in Granada (Andalucia), which was followed by a motorcade. The event was part of a nationwide farmers' demonstration movement against the ratification of the EU's free-trade agreements until partner third countries comply with the EU's agricultural standards, and in favor of fair production prices for Spanish farmers, relief measures to offset the consequences of droughts and of the import of agricultural products from Ukraine, as well as better working and social conditions in their sector.

notes: On 18 March 2024, 250 farmers with around 35 tractors participated in a motorcade in Huelva (Andalucia). The event was part of a nationwide farmers' demonstration movement, called by UPA, COAG, Agro-Food Cooperatives (Cooperativas Agroalimentarias) and ASAJA against the ratification of the EU's free-trade agreements until partner third countries comply with the EU's agricultural standards, and in favor of fair production prices for Spanish farmers, relief measures to offset the consequences of droughts and the import of agricultural products from Ukraine, as well as better working and social conditions in their sector.
notes_wrapped:
On 18 March 2024, 250 farmers with around 35
tractors participated in a motorcade in Huelva
(Andalucia). The event was part of a nationwide
farmers' demonstration movement, called by UPA,
COAG, Agro-Food Cooperatives (Cooperativas
Agroalimentarias) and ASAJA against the
ratification of the EU's free-trade agreements
until partner third countries comply with the EU's
agricultural standards, and in favor of fair
production prices for Spanish farmers, relief
measures to offset the consequences of droughts
and the import of agricultural products from
Ukraine, as well as better working and social
conditions in their sector.

notes: On 27 March 2024, about 50 people, including a farmer and the mayor (FW), participated in a motorcade and protest starting in Neuruppin through Lindow to Rheinsberg and back to Neuruppin (Brandenburg) for peace, subsidies, agricultural diesel and against NATO and the federal coalition government. The protesters also demanded that tax money should be invested in Germany and in development aid for other countries or arms purchases for Ukraine. The event was part of a nationwide demonstration movement against the federal government and its economic and agricultural policies.

notes: On 27 March 2024, at the call of a regional citizens' initiative, around 100 people, including farmers and representatives of the alliance 'United' (FAIReint), with 30 tractors participated in a protest in front of an event hall in Wesendorf (Niedersachsen) for diversity and against the AfD, right-wing populism and racism. The context of the protest was a citizens' dialogue of AfD that was taking place simultaneously. The protest was organized following reports about a secret meeting between AfD members and far-right activists in Potsdam in November 2023, during which remigration plans were discussed.

notes: On 27 March 2024, more than 50 farmers, called by COAG and UPA, held a protest in Zaragoza (Aragon). The event was part of a nationwide farmers' demonstration movement against the ratification of the EU's free-trade agreements until partner third countries comply with the EU's agricultural standards, and in favor of fair production prices for Spanish farmers, relief measures to offset the consequences of droughts and of the import of agricultural products from Ukraine, as well as better working and social conditions in their sector.

notes: On 31 March 2024, farmers, livestock breeders and beekeepers of Thessaly, rallied at the monument marking the Kileler Uprising on the 114th anniversary of the revolt. They had lined-up their tractors at the site from the previous night to prevent any state event from taking place. Their representatives made statements demanding solutions from the government and not just words.
